-- Monte Paschi's Main Investor Says Bank's Capital Sufficient, Sole Reports
-- B y   A r m o r e l   K e n n a
-- 2010-10-28T06:46:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-28/monte-paschi-s-main-investor-says-bank-s-capital-sufficient-sole-reports.html
Banca Monte dei Paschi di Siena SpA 
doesn’t need to raise capital, said Gabriello Mancini, chairman
of the bank’s biggest investor, Fondazione Monte dei Paschi,
according to daily Il Sole 24 Ore.  “Much has already been done to strengthen the bank’s
assets,” Mancini said, according to the Italian newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
